comments: Dort (OKC) slides his hand across and off Wood's (DAL) body, which does not affect his FOM in the lane.
Finney-Smith (DAL) is moving alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and absorbs the body contact as they come together during the drive.
Finney-Smith (DAL) jumps from point A to point B and initiates contact with Wiggins' (OKC) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
As Dort (OKC) is attempting to deflect the pass, contact occurs with Doncic's (DAL) head/face area, which affects Doncic's ability to pass.
Doncic (DAL) legally contests Wiggins' (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Bullock (DAL) and Joe (OKC) come together as both players pursue the loose ball.
As Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) slows his momentum on the drive, he releases away from Finney-Smith (DAL), and the contact is marginal.
Doncic (DAL) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt.
Bullock (DAL) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path and does not deliver any contact.
Dort (OKC) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Bullock (DAL) remains inbounds when he receives the pass near the sideline.
As Finney-Smith (DAL) moves toward the rebound, marginal contact occurs with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) arm, which does not affect his ability to secure the loose ball.
Finney-Smith (DAL) legally contests Joe's (OKC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Wood (DAL) does not establish himself in Dort's (OKC) path when contact occurs to Dort's side/back on the screen.
Doncic (DAL) establishes himself in Wiggins' (OKC) path and does not deliver any contact.
Dort (OKC) is moving alongside Doncic's (DAL) path, and marginal contact occurs when Doncic releases at the end of his drive.
Dort (OKC) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) jump shot attempt.
